\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f2\lang2057 
\par 24 Bit Version
\par --------------
\par If your computer starts up in the 24 bit version of the game with fuzzy
\par looking graphics, try re-selecting the screen mode from the F11 menu. This
\par should cure this problem.
\par 
\par High colour GTA uses a built-in version of the "univbe" display driver to
\par provide its multitude of 15, 16 and 32-bit display modes. If your video card
\par is not recognised by the univbe check, or if you change your video card and
\par the check does not update to it, try running uvconfig.exe in the gtados
\par directory. If that doesn't work, try running 24-bit GTA by typing
\par "gta24 -nounivbe" in the gtados directory. This will cause it to skip univbe
\par and use your video card's native drivers instead. Alternatively, get hold of
\par the latest version of univbe from SciTech Software, and run it as a TSR before
\par running GTA.
\par 
\par Windows Drivers ( Grand Theft Auto DirectX )
\par ---------------
\par GTA DirectX will only work correctly if you have the latest Windows 95 Direct
\par X Microsoft-certified driver for your video card. Your video card vendor
\par should be able to supply this.
\par 
\par Some of the latest versions of drivers will allow the use of
\par High colour / Low resolution screen modes (recommended). An example of this
\par is the Matrox Millenium.
\par 
\par Gravis Ultrasound
\par -----------------
\par 
\par The DOS version of GTA, run under Windows 95, will not play any
\par sound effects with an Ultrasound, UNLESS you shut down windows into MS-DOS
\par mode, or change the PIF from DOS-Box to MS-DOS mode.
\par 
\par DOS Version - CD Sound
\par ----------------------
\par To allow CD audio to play on the DOS version of GTA, when run under a
\par bootable version of DOS, make sure that you have the MSCDEX driver loaded. 
\par On a Windows 95 machine, if you play the DOS version through Windows, or
\par in a DOS box, you should get CD audio.
\par 
\par Sidewinder Control Pad - In DOS GTA
\par -----------------------------------
\par The Microsoft Sidewinder pad is not compatible with DOS GTA. However, it
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f2\lang2057 can be used with Windows (DirectX) GTA.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f2\lang2057 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f2\lang2057 Voodoo Graphics (3Dfx) Users
\par ----------------------------
\par GTA supports 3Dfx Glide 2.42 and higher. Voodoo Graphics users must have
\par this updated version of Glide installed on their system. To install the
\par updated Glide runtime driver kit, run the grtvgr.exe file in the 3Dfx
\par }{\f2\lang2057 folder of the GTA CD.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f2\lang2057 Note that we recommend 32MB of RAM to run 3DFX GTA.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\widctlpar\adjustright {\f2\lang2057 
\par EMM386 (DOS)
\par ------------
\par In DOS 6.22, If you have the line DEVICE=C:\\DOS\\EMM386.EXE in your CONFIG.SYS,
\par play GTA, quit then press Ctrl-Alt-Del to reset the machine, you may find
\par that the keyboard does not respond any more.
\par 
\par Using DEVICE=C:\\WINDOWS\\EMM386.EXE instead should solve this problem. 
